Summary:

Entirety of the code is contained in one single python script file:
 ./git_http_backend/GitHttpBackend.py
It can be used both, as a Python module and as a command-line executable.

The simplest way to run the server is to "double-click" on that py file
in your file browser. See output of "--help" for options.

Installation and running instructions:

1. Check out latest git_http_backend.py repo:
	git clone git://github.com/dvdotsenko/git_http_backend.py.git ghbpy
2. (Optional) Copy one file to place of convenience:
	(Windows:) copy .\ghbpy\git_http_backend\GitHttpBackend.py c:\tools\
	(*nix) cp ./ghbpy/git_http_backend/GitHttpBackend.py ~/bin/
3. Run the script with "--help" option to see the list of options and examples.
	c:\tools\GitHttpBackend.py --help
	~\bin\GitHttpBackend.py --help
4. Run the same script with chosen options (or without any) to run the server.
